annotationA: Deacetylase activity; histone deacetylase activity; zinc ion binding. It is involved in the biological process described with: tricarboxylic acid cycle; respiratory electron transport chain; regulation of transcription, DNA-templated; histone deacetylation; neurotransmitter secretion
annotationB: Sirtuin 2 is an NAD-dependent histone deacetylase in the class I of the Sirtuin family. It is involved in protein deacetylation, determination of adult lifespan, and neurodegeneration
